basic.Peptide Name: Human alpha-synuclein (Alpha-Syn, antimicrobial protein; natural AMPs; primates, mammals, animals; UCLL1a; BBBh2o)
basic.Target Organism: Active against bacteria E. coli (MIC 0.2 uM), P. aeruginosa (MIC 0.2 uM), S. aureus (MIC 0.2 uM), S. epidermidis (MIC 0.2 uM), yeast C. albicans (MIC 0.4 uM), C. tropicalis (MIC 0.4 uM), F. neoformans (MIC 0.8 uM), mold A. flavus (MIC 0.8 uM), A. fumigatus (MIC 1.6 uM), A. parasiticus (MIC 1.6 uM), R. solani (MIC 3.2 uM), and T. harzianum (MIC 3.2 uM).
